16/07/2007
SKOPJE, Macedonia â Former Foreign Minister Srgjan Kerim, president-elect of the UN General Assembly, says his priorities will be fighting terrorism, monitoring climate changes and reforming the UN during his term, which begins in September. 
He told Radio Free Europe at the weekend that his election to the post is an honour to both him and his country. 
He also denied that he would run for president of Macedonia in 2009. 
